LOCAL RENDERING (Your Machine)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Show progress summary
npm run render:master -- --summary

# Render ONE random quiz
npm run render:master -- --one

# Render ALL unrendered quizzes
npm run render:master -- --all

# Show help
npm run render:master -- --help

# Run without arguments to get the menu
npm run render:master

# Reset stuck videos first (recommended):
npm run render:master -- --reset

# Then start parallel rendering:
npm run render:master -- --all


VAST.AI GPU RENDERING (Cloud Instance) ⚡
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GPU-accelerated rendering is now configured! See these files:

📖 START_HERE_VASTAI.md          - Quick start guide (READ THIS FIRST!)
📖 CHEATSHEET.txt                - Quick reference commands
📖 VAST_AI_COMMANDS.txt          - Complete command reference
📖 LOCAL_DOWNLOAD_GUIDE.txt      - How to download videos
📖 VAST_AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md       - Detailed technical docs

✅ GPU settings configured in:
   - remotion.config.ts (ANGLE renderer, GPU acceleration)
   - scripts/masterRender.ts (Chromium GPU flags)

🚀 Expected performance on Vast.ai:
   - 30-60 seconds per video (vs 2-3 min without GPU)
   - 430 videos in 14-28 hours
   - Cost: ~$7-28 total

QUICK STEPS FOR VAST.AI:
1. Connect: ssh -p <PORT> root@<IP>
2. Setup: See START_HERE_VASTAI.md
3. Test: npm run render:master -- --one
4. Render: npm run render:master -- --all
5. Download: Use LOCAL_DOWNLOAD_GUIDE.txt

